<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-4 new-resource-directions">
		<h3 class="form-heading">Guidelines</h3>
		<p>Adding a resource simply means providing a link and a description of the resource that the link connects us to.</p>
		<p>Ideal resources are links to: research papers, well researched news articles, documentaries, pdfs, powerpoints, reports, public policy documents, websites, or technologies that can be used for something (ex: the bailout app, a crowdfunding website, a--hopefully free--online course).</p> 
		<p>Before adding a resource ensure that the resource does the following:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Provides detailed and thorough information.</li>
			<li>Includes supporting evidence and/or references to sources.</li>
			<li>Belongs to an author, publication, or website that can be verified or contacted for further information.</li>
		</ul>
		<p></p>
		<p>Within your description provide a brief objective summary of the resource rather than an opinion or review.</p>
		<p>Hopefully your resource is FREE to the public. If it is not, please mention that in your description.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-8 new-resource-form">
	    <h3 class="form-heading">New Resource Form</h3>
		<%= form_for @resource, url: {action: "create"}, html: {class: "resource_form"} do |f| %>
			<div class="res-input">
				<%= f.label "Title (Max 100 characters)" %><br/>
				<%= f.text_field :title, size: "80x2" %>
			</div>
			<div class="res-input">
				<%= f.label "Url (copy and paste the exact web address including the http:// part at the beginning or else your link may not work)" %><br/>
				<%= f.text_area :url, size: "80x2" %>
			</div>
			<div class="res-input">
				<%= f.label "Description (Max 600 characters)" %><br/>
				<%= f.text_area :description, size: "80x12" %>
			</div>
			<div class="res-input">
				<%= f.label "Select a Category"%>
				<%= f.select :category_id, options_from_collection_for_select(@categories, 'id', 'title')%>
			</div>
		  	<%= f.submit "Create" %>
		<% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
